ate` to `EventType` iota (after existing types)\\n- Add case to `String()` method\\n\\n### 2. Add model hint storage functions\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/session_state.go`\\n- `StoreModelHint(ctx, sessionID, model)` — writes `.git/entire-sessions/{session_id}.model`\\n- `LoadModelHint(ctx, sessionID) string` — reads model hint, returns \\\"\\\" on error\\n- Update `ClearSessionState` to also remove the `.model` hint file\\n\\n### 3. Claude Code: capture model from SessionStart\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/types.go`\\n- Add `Model string \\\\`json:\\\"model\\\"\\\\`` to `sessionInfoRaw`\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go`\\n- In `parseSessionStart`: set `Event.Model = raw.Model`\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle_test.go`\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_SessionStart_IncludesModel` — SessionStart with model field\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_SessionStart_EmptyModel` — SessionStart without model (backward compat)\\n\\n### 4. Gemini CLI: capture model from BeforeModel\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/types.go`\\n- Add `beforeModelRaw` struct with `SessionID`, `TranscriptPath`, and nested `LLMRequest struct { Model string }`\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/lifecycle.go`\\n- Change `HookNameBeforeModel` from pass-through to parsing `beforeModelRaw`\\n- Return `agent.Event{Type: ModelUpdate, SessionID, Model}` when model is present\\n- Return nil when model is empty (graceful fallback)\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/lifecycle_test.go`\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_BeforeModel_ReturnsModelUpdate` — model present\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_BeforeModel_EmptyModel_ReturnsNil` — no model, still pass-through\\n- Update `TestParseHookEvent_PassThroughHooks_ReturnNil` to remove `HookNameBeforeModel`\\n- Update `TestParseHookEvent_AllLifecycleHooks` table to include BeforeModel → ModelUpdate\\n\\n### 5. Lifecycle: model hint integration\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go`\\n- Add `handleLifecycleModelUpdate(ctx, ag, event)` — stores model hint via `strategy.StoreModelHint`\\n- Add `case agent.ModelUpdate:` to `DispatchLifecycleEvent`\\n- In `handleLifecycleSessionStart`: if `event.Model != \\\"\\\"`, store hint + update existing state's `ModelName`\\n- In `handleLifecycleTurnStart`: if `event.Model == \\\"\\\"`, read hint → use as model arg to `InitializeSession`\\n- In `handleLifecycleTurnEnd`: if `event.Model == \\\"\\\"`, read hint → use as model arg to `transitionSessionTurnEnd`\\n\\n### 6. Review fixes\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/transcript.go`\\n- Add `slog.Warn` for `json.Unmarshal` error in `ExtractModelFromTranscript` (distinguish corrupt from missing)\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/transcript_test.go`\\n- Add `TestExtractModelFromTranscript_CorruptSettingsFile`\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\\n- Add doc comment line for `model` parameter on `InitializeSession`\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_session.go`\\n- Add doc comment line for `model` parameter on `initializeSession`\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\\n```\\n\\nManually verify:\\n- All existing tests still pass\\n- New tests cover model propagation for Claude Code and Gemini\\n- Model hint files are created/read correctly\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alex/.claude/projects/-Users-alex-workspace-cli--worktrees-1/56599601-5154-4a0e-9c52-994cebb11f88.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"56b0d50e-3a9f-445e-b0b8-49278361a0e1\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T05:30:01.588Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Plan: Add model tracking for Claude Code and Gemini CLI agents\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nPR #581 adds LLM model name tracking to session info, but missed two agents:\\n- **Claude Code**: Sends `model` in `SessionStart` hook payload (confirmed in docs)\\n- **Gemini CLI**: Sends `llm_request.model` in `BeforeModel` hook payload (confirmed in docs)\\n\\nBoth agents deliver model info on hooks that fire as **separate CLI processes** from TurnStart/TurnEnd. We need cross-process persistence for the model value.\\n\\nAdditionally, the PR review identified several secondary issues to fix.\\n\\n## Design: Model Hint Files\\n\\nStore model in `.git/entire-sessions/{session_id}.model` — a tiny text file that persists across hook invocations within the same session:\\n- **Written by**: `handleLifecycleSessionStart` (Claude Code), `handleLifecycleModelUpdate` (Gemini)\\n- **Read by**: `handleLifecycleTurnStart` and `handleLifecycleTurnEnd` when `event.Model == \\\"\\\"`\\n- **Cleaned up**: Alongside session state file cleanup (existing mechanism)\\n\\n## Steps\\n\\n### 1. Add `ModelUpdate` event type\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go`\\n- Add `ModelUpdate` to `EventType` iota (after existing types)\\n- Add case to `String()` method\\n\\n### 2. Add model hint storage functions\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/session_state.go`\\n- `StoreModelHint(ctx, sessionID, model)` — writes `.git/entire-sessions/{session_id}.model`\\n- `LoadModelHint(ctx, sessionID) string` — reads model hint, returns \\\"\\\" on error\\n- Update `ClearSessionState` to also remove the `.model` hint file\\n\\n### 3. Claude Code: capture model from SessionStart\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/types.go`\\n- Add `Model string \\\\`json:\\\"model\\\"\\\\`` to `sessionInfoRaw`\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go`\\n- In `parseSessionStart`: set `Event.Model = raw.Model`\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle_test.go`\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_SessionStart_IncludesModel` — SessionStart with model field\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_SessionStart_EmptyModel` — SessionStart without model (backward compat)\\n\\n### 4. Gemini CLI: capture model from BeforeModel\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/types.go`\\n- Add `beforeModelRaw` struct with `SessionID`, `TranscriptPath`, and nested `LLMRequest struct { Model string }`\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/lifecycle.go`\\n- Change `HookNameBeforeModel` from pass-through to parsing `beforeModelRaw`\\n- Return `agent.Event{Type: ModelUpdate, SessionID, Model}` when model is present\\n- Return nil when model is empty (graceful fallback)\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/lifecycle_test.go`\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_BeforeModel_ReturnsModelUpdate` — model present\\n- `TestParseHookEvent_BeforeModel_EmptyModel_ReturnsNil` — no model, still pass-through\\n- Update `TestParseHookEvent_PassThroughHooks_ReturnNil` to remove `HookNameBeforeModel`\\n- Update `TestParseHookEvent_AllLifecycleHooks` table to include BeforeModel → ModelUpdate\\n\\n### 5. Lifecycle: model hint integration\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go`\\n- Add `handleLifecycleModelUpdate(ctx, ag, event)` — stores model hint via `strategy.StoreModelHint`\\n- Add `case agent.ModelUpdate:` to `DispatchLifecycleEvent`\\n- In `handleLifecycleSessionStart`: if `event.Model != \\\"\\\"`, store hint + update existing state's `ModelName`\\n- In `handleLifecycleTurnStart`: if `event.Model == \\\"\\\"`, read hint → use as model arg to `InitializeSession`\\n- In `handleLifecycleTurnEnd`: if `event.Model == \\\"\\\"`, read hint → use as model arg to `transitionSessionTurnEnd`\\n\\n### 6. Review fixes\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/transcript.go`\\n- Add `slog.Warn` for `json.Unmarshal` error in `ExtractModelFromTranscript` (distinguish corrupt from missing)\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/transcript_test.go`\\n- Add `TestExtractModelFromTranscript_CorruptSettingsFile`\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\\n- Add doc comment line for `model` parameter on `InitializeSession`\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_session.go`\\n- Add doc comment 