asic metadata (session_id, model, start time, agent type, etc.)\\n2. **TurnStart**: Fill in the git-specific fields (base_commit, worktree_path, shadow branch setup, etc.)\\n\\nThis is a cleaner design than the hint file approach. Let me think about the implications:\\n\\n**Benefits:**\\n- No separate `.model` file to manage\\n- All session metadata lives in one place (the state JSON)\\n- Works for all agents uniformly\\n- `SessionStart` becomes a real \\\"initialize session\\\" step, which makes semantic sense\\n\\n\\n- The state file would exist earlier, which opens up possibilities like showing session status before the first prompt\\n\\n**What needs to change:**\\n- `handleLifecycleSessionStart` needs to create a minimal session state if one doesn't exist\\n- `InitializeSession` (on TurnStart) needs to handle an existing state with empty `BaseCommit` — it already does! It falls through to `initializeSession()` when `state.BaseCommit == \\\"\\\"`\\n- `initializeSession` needs to preserve fields from the existing partial state (model, start time, agent type) when creating the full state\\n\\nI'm starting to think through the potential concerns with this approach.\\n\\nThe main risk is that other parts of the system might not handle a partial state gracefully — things like `CountOtherActiveSessionsWithCheckpoints`, session listing, and other operations could break if they encounter empty fields like `BaseCommit` or `WorktreePath`. Also, with this approach the state exists by the time `BeforeModel` fires, so I can just update `state.ModelName` directly instead of needing a hint file.\\n\\nNow I'm figuring out what the minimal state should actually contain: `SessionID`, `ModelName`, `StartedAt`, `AgentType`, and `Phase` — though I need to decide what phase value makes sense when the session starts but hasn't entered the main turn loop yet.\\n\\nLooking at the existing code, `handleLifecycleSessionStart` already fires `EventSessionStart` on the state, and `InitializeSession` handles the case where state exists but `BaseCommit` is empty. The user's suggestion makes sense, so I should discuss this design change rather than jump straight into implementation.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":174,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":152614,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":174},\"output_tokens\":12,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYfeTQswv67UVSWGHoRTh\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"7b5a98a7-6de2-4cd3-84e5-1e2a5108071d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T06:08:15.880Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"7b5a98a7-6de2-4cd3-84e5-1e2a5108071d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/1\",\"sessionId\":\"993f4b55-d917-4933-8513-05c115a0f7ef\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"feat/model-in-session-info\",\"slug\":\"crispy-sprouting-cake\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_015Uiif3x4cuifUgGK2pyBff\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"That's a much cleaner design. The session state file becomes the single source of truth from the start, no extra files to manage.\\n\\nThe split would look like:\\n\\n**SessionStart** (all agents) — create minimal state:\\n- `SessionID`, `StartedAt`, `AgentType`, `ModelName`, `Phase`\\n- Basically: \\\"a session exists, here's what we know so far\\\"\\n\\n**TurnStart** (`InitializeSession`) — fill in git-specific fields:\\n- `BaseCommit`, `WorktreePath`, `WorktreeID`, `TurnID`, shadow branch setup, etc.\\n- This already handles `state != nil && state.BaseCommit == \\\"\\\"` by falling through to `initializeSession()`\\n\\nThe key change in `initializeSession` would be: if a partial state already exists (from SessionStart), carry forward the fields it set (model, start time, etc.) instead of overwriting t