d `handleLifecycleModelUpdate`, wired `ModelUpdate` dispatch, added hint reads to TurnStart/TurnEnd, added hint write to SessionStart\\n   - Step 6: Added `slog.Warn` for corrupt settings in factoryaidroid, doc comments for model params, test for corrupt settings\\n\\n3. Lint error: `wrapcheck` linter caught unwrapped `os.WriteFile` return in `StoreModelHint`. Fixed by wrapping with `fmt.Errorf`.\\n\\n4. All tests passed (`mise run test:ci`).\\n\\n5. User feedback - CRITICAL DESIGN DISCUSSION:\\n   - User asked: \\\"can't we...put the model into the session state file as opposed to another file we need to manage?\\\"\\n   - I explained the timing issue: Claude Code's SessionStart fires before the state file exists\\n   - User asked: \\\"is the problem just around the timing of the session state file creation?\\\"\\n   - I confirmed yes\\n   - User asked about per-turn model settings for Gemini and other agents\\n   - I provided a table showing all agents' model delivery mechanisms\\n   - User asked: \\\"do all agents have the concept of a 'startSession'?\\\" - Yes, all 5 do\\n   - User suggested: \\\"perhaps we could split the session file creation into two parts - the initialisation (timestamps, model, startTime) at startSession and the rest where it is now on turnStart?\\\"\\n   - I launched an explore agent to investigate empty BaseCommit impact\\n   - The investigation found that empty BaseCommit would break: shadow branch naming, checkpoint writing, doctor classification, SaveStep recovery\\n   - User asked: \\\"and once we read the model we stick it into the session state?\\\" - I confirmed yes\\n   - User said: \\\"ok fine.\\\" - accepted the hint file approach\\n   - User asked: \\\"can we break this up into a few commits?\\\" - I proposed 5 commits\\n\\n6. I then:\\n   - Updated the `StoreModelHint` doc comment with full rationale for why a separate file\\n   - Refactored `handleLifecycleModelUpdate` to prefer direct state update when state exists, only falling back to hint file\\n   - Ran fmt + lint (clean)\\n   - Made commit 1: event type + hint storage (event.go, session_state.go)\\n   - Made commit 2: Claude Code model capture (types.go, lifecycle.go, lifecycle_test.go)\\n\\nRemaining commits:\\n3. Gemini CLI model capture\\n4. Lifecycle wiring\\n5. Review fixes\\n\\nLet me document all the specific files and changes carefully.\\n\\nSummary:\\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\\n   The user asked to implement a plan from PR #581 that adds LLM model name tracking for Claude Code and Gemini CLI agents. The plan was provided in full at the start. After implementation, the user engaged in a design discussion about whether to use a separate `.model` hint file vs putting the model into the session state file. After investigation showed that creating a partial session state (with empty BaseCommit) would break multiple systems, the user accepted the hint file approach but requested thorough documentation of *why* it exists. The user then asked to break the changes into multiple commits.\\n\\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\\n   - **Cross-process persistence**: Each hook invocation (SessionStart, TurnStart, TurnEnd, BeforeModel) runs as a separate CLI process — no shared memory between them\\n   - **Model hint file**: `.git/entire-sessions/{session_id}.model` — a lightweight text file bridging the gap between model arrival (SessionStart/BeforeModel) and session state creation (TurnStart)\\n   - **SessionState requires BaseCommit**: BaseCommit is deeply wired as a required field used for shadow branch naming, checkpoint writing, doctor classification. Empty BaseCommit would produce invalid branch names like `entire/-<hash>`\\n   - **Agent model delivery timing**:\\n     - OpenCode, Cursor: model on TurnStart + TurnEnd (state exists)\\n     - Factory AI Droid: model on TurnStart + TurnEnd + `.settings.json` fallback (state exists)\\n     - Claude Code: model on SessionStart only (state does NOT exist yet)\\n     - Gemini CLI: model on BeforeModel (state exists — fires after TurnStart)\\n   - **ModelUpdate event type**: New lifecycle event for hooks that carry model info but have no other lifecycle significance\\n   - All 5 agents (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, OpenCode, Cursor, Factory AI Droid) have SessionStart\\n\\n3. Files and Code Sections:\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go`** — Added `ModelUpdate` event type\\n     - Added to `EventType` iota after `SubagentEnd`\\n     - Added case to `String()` method\\n     ```go\\n     // ModelUpdate indicates the agent reported the LLM model being used.\\n     ModelUpdate\\n     ```\\n     ```go\\n     case ModelUpdate:\\n         return \\\"ModelUpdate\\\"\\n     ```\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/session_state.go`** — Model hint file storage + cleanup\\n     - Added `StoreModelHint(ctx, sessionID, model)` with full doc comment explaining why a separate file is needed\\n     - Added `LoadModelHint(ctx, sessionID) string`\\n     - Updated `ClearSessionState` to also remove `.model` hint file\\n     - Final doc comment on `StoreModelHint`:\\n     ```go\\n     // StoreModelHint writes the LLM model name to a lightweight hint file\\n     // (.git/entire-sessions/{session_id}.model) for cross-process persistence.\\n     //\\n     // Why a separate file instead of SessionState?\\n     //\\n     // SessionState requires BaseCommit (used for shadow branch naming, checkpoint\\n     // writing, doctor classification, etc.) and is only created during TurnStart\\n     // when the git repo is fully inspected. Some agents report the model on earlier\\n     // hooks that fire as separate CLI processes before TurnStart:\\n     //\\n     //   - Claude Code sends \\\"model\\\" on SessionStart (before any TurnStart)\\n     //   - Gemini CLI sends \\\"llm_request.model\\\" on BeforeModel (after TurnStart,\\n     //     so handleLifecycleModelUpdate writes to SessionState directly when it\\n     //     exists and only falls back to this hint file otherwise)\\n     //\\n     // The hint is read by handleLifecycleTurnStart/TurnEnd when event.Model is\\n     // empty, passed to InitializeSession, and persisted in state.ModelName. After\\n     // that the hint file is redundant — it sits unused until ClearSessionState\\n     // removes it alongside the session state file.\\n     ```\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/types.go`** — Added `Model` field to `sessionInfoRaw`\\n     ```go\\n     type sessionInfoRaw struct {\\n         SessionID      string `json:\\\"session_id\\\"`\\n         TranscriptPath string `json:\\\"transcript_path\\\"`\\n         Model          string `json:\\\"model,omitempty\\\"`\\n     }\\n     ```\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go`** — Updated `parseSessionStart` to populate `Event.Model`\\n     ```go\\n     return &agent.Event{\\n         Type:       agent.SessionStart,\\n         SessionID:  raw.SessionID,\\n         SessionRef: raw.TranscriptPath,\\n         Model:      raw.Model,\\n         Timestamp:  time.Now(),\\n     }, nil\\n     ```\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle_test.go`** — Added 2 tests\\n     - `TestParseHookEvent_SessionStart_IncludesModel` — verifies model field is parsed\\n     - `TestParseHookEvent_SessionStart_EmptyModel` — verifies backward compat when model absent\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/types.go`** — Added `beforeModelRaw` struct\\n     ```go\\n     type beforeModelRaw struct {\\n         SessionID      string `json:\\\"session_id\\\"`\\n         TranscriptPath string `json:\\\"transcript_path\\\"`\\n         LLMRequest     struct {\\n             Model string `json:\\\"model\\\"`\\n         } `json:\\\"llm_request\\\"`\\n     }\\n     ```\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/lifecycle.go`** — Changed BeforeModel from pass-through to parsed\\n     - Moved `HookNameBeforeModel` out of the pass-through case into its own `case` calling `g.parseBeforeModel(stdin)`\\n     - Added `parseBeforeModel` method returning `ModelUpdate` event when model is present, nil when empty\\n     ```go\\n     func (g *GeminiCLIAgent) parseBeforeModel(stdin io.Reader) (*agent.Event, error) {\\n         raw, err := agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[beforeModelRaw](stdin)\\n         if err != nil {\\n             return nil, err\\n         }\\n         model := raw.LLMRequest.Model\\n         if model == \\\"\\\" {\\n             return nil, nil\\n         }\\n         return &agent.Event{\\n             Type:      agent.ModelUpdate,\\n             SessionID: raw.SessionID,\\n             Model:     model,\\n             Timestamp: time.Now(),\\n         }, nil\\n     }\\n     ```\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/lifecycle_test.go`** — Added/updated tests\\n     - `TestParseHookEvent_BeforeModel_ReturnsModelUpdate` — model present → ModelUpdate event\\n     - `TestParseHookEvent_BeforeModel_EmptyModel_ReturnsNil` — empty model → nil event\\n     - Removed `HookNameBeforeModel` from `TestParseHookEvent_PassThroughHooks_ReturnNil`\\n     - Updated `TestParseHookEvent_AllLifecycleHooks` table: BeforeModel now expects `ModelUpdate` with `llm_request` payload instead of `expectNil: true`\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go`** — Lifecycle wiring for model hints\\n     - Added `case agent.ModelUpdate:` to `DispatchLifecycleEvent`\\n     - Added `handleLifecycleModelUpdate` — prefers direct state update, falls back to hint file\\n     - Updated `handleLifecycleSessionStart` — stores hint when `event.Model != \\\"\\\"`, updates state.ModelName if state exists\\n     - Updated `handleLifecycleTurnStart` — reads hint when `event.Model == \\\"\\\"`\\n     - Updated `handleLifecycleTurnEnd` — reads hint when `event.Model == \\\"\\\"`\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/transcript.go`** — Added `slog.Warn` for corrupt settings JSON\\n     ```go\\n     if err := json.Unmarshal(data, &settings); err != nil {\\n         slog.Warn(\\\"corrupt settings file, cannot extract model\\\",\\n             slog.String(\\\"path\\\", settingsPath),\\n             slog.Any(\\\"error\\\", err))\\n         return \\\"\\\"\\n     }\\n     ```\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/transcript_test.go`** — Added `TestExtractModelFromTranscript_CorruptSettingsFile`\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`** — Added doc comment for `model` param on `InitializeSession`\\n\\n   - **`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_session.go`** — Added doc comment for `model` param on `initializeSession`\\n\\n4. Errors and fixes:\\n   - **`wrapcheck` lint error**: `StoreModelHint` returned `os.WriteFile(...)` directly. The `wrapcheck` linter requires wrapping errors from external packages. Fixed by wrapping: `if err := os.WriteFile(...); err != nil { return fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to write model hint file: %w\\\", err) }`.\\n   - **User feedback on design**: User pushed back on the `.model` hint file, asking why not use the session state file. This led to a thorough investigation of empty BaseCommit impact, which showed it would break shadow branch naming, checkpoint writing, doctor classification, and SaveStep recovery. User accepted the hint file approach after seeing the evidence but insisted on thorough documentation.\\n   - **User feedback on `handleLifecycleModelUpdate`**: During the design discussion, I refined this function to prefer direct state update when the state file exists (Gemini's case) and only fall back to the hint file when state doesn't exist yet (Claude Code's case).\\n\\n5. Problem Solving:\\n   - Solved the cross-process model persistence problem using hint files\\n   - Investigated and documented why a partial SessionState (empty BaseCommit) approach won't work\\n   - Refined `handleLifecycleModelUpdate` to avoid unnecessary hint file writes when state exists\\n\\n6. All user messages:\\n   - \\\"Implement the following plan: [detailed plan for model tracking]\\\"\\n   - \\\"can't we...put the model into the session s